# Free key from https://www.alphavantage.co/support/#api-key — powers the التغيرات الاقتصادية
# card (oil / natural gas / gold / USD-SAR). Free tier = 25 requests/day, so results are
# cached ~4h. WITHOUT this key the card automatically falls back to the World Bank API
# (keyless macro indicators — inflation / GDP growth), so it still shows REAL data.
VITE_ALPHAVANTAGE_API_KEY=

# Local Ollama server powering the "AI Analyze" button in each widget (gpt-oss:20b by default).
# Also enriches official statements (summary/category/urgency/entities). Optional — both
# default in code; falls back to a keyword heuristic when unavailable.
# VITE_OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434
# VITE_OLLAMA_MODEL=gpt-oss:20b

# ── Backend (server-side) — used by the /api/statements proxy, NOT the browser ──
# Free, approved appname for the ReliefWeb API v2 (register at
# https://apidoc.reliefweb.int/parameters#appname). Without it ReliefWeb 403s and the
# proxy simply serves GDELT + official RSS instead. No VITE_ prefix — read via process.env.
# RELIEFWEB_APPNAME=your-approved-appname

# ── Security Threats section — ACLED is the ONLY data source ────────────────
# (BACKEND ONLY — credentials never reach the browser). Register free at
# https://developer.acleddata.com. Provide EITHER a pre-generated access
# token, OR email + password (OAuth2 password grant). Missing/unreachable →
# the card just shows its generic "couldn't load" or empty state, never a
# technical/config error.
# ACLED_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# ACLED_EMAIL=
# ACLED_PASSWORD=
# ACLED_CLIENT_ID=acled
# ACLED_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ── Flight tracking (حركة الطيران layer) — OpenSky Network ──────────────────
# (BACKEND ONLY — never reaches the browser; used by the /api/opensky proxy.)
# OpenSky moved to OAuth2 in 2025 and now rate-limits ANONYMOUS access to almost
# nothing (HTTP 429), so the flight layer shows no aircraft without credentials.
# Create a FREE OAuth2 API client under your OpenSky account
# (https://opensky-network.org/ → Account → API Client) and put the pair here.
# Legacy basic-auth (username/password) still works as a fallback if you have it.
# OPENSKY_CLIENT_ID=
# OPENSKY_CLIENT_SECRET=
# OPENSKY_USERNAME=
# OPENSKY_PASSWORD=
# Optional bounding box (defaults cover Africa→Europe→Middle East→S/C Asia):
# OPENSKY_LAMIN=0
# OPENSKY_LOMIN=-15
# OPENSKY_LAMAX=60
# OPENSKY_LOMAX=100
